defaultQ42 default&#xa0; 
defaultChair:default And it never happened in the first place. There was already evidence of leaks of methane into the tap water in that area.
defaultProfessor Thomasdefault: I think it has to be said that we have a solid regulatory system. If Richard’s predictions are correct—and that is a big, big if—you would have to scale up the capability to regulate, to manage and to inspect, but we are not there yet. That is part of the risk development and risk escalation phase—whatever the right phrase is.
